reviews.review: The Rise of Skywalker is more than just tying up the loose ends of the most recent trilogy, it is a finality, a swan song of sorts for the entire anthology.  Once again Abrams delivered the goods.

This movie was wonderful. 

The fact that critics are rating it so low goes to show that the vocal and toxic minority in the Star Wars universe are not the fans, but the critics themselves.

There were horses on top of spaceships, laser crossbows and women with electric hands. And there were robots made of balls and robots with only one wheel.  There were many, MANY extra-large guns, and goofy looking aliens scattered about like it ain't no thing. The baddies lost and the goodies won, which was especially nice as it certainly looked like the mouldy old man had it in the bag at one point. There were bigger waves than I've ever seen, which was enjoyable, especially when two people chose that spot for a fight made of fire-swords! One spaceship landed actually on fire and they all got out and had bants about it, while very many others burned in sadder ways, especially the one the monkey was on.  But then he wasn't so that turned out ace! I thought all the lead characters were great folks, just the kind of people I'd like to hang out with, except for that they would probably get me killed.  If you like all these things you will love this film.  I did.

I was 14 when the first Star Wars movie was released. I watched it 7 times at the theatre. Itâ€™s great to see a positive conclusion with the Rebellion winning, but also sadly the end of a great part of my childhood. Thank you George Lucas!

I honestly walked in expecting to hate the movie, and with how rushed the beginning of the movie was, I was feeling like I was going to be right. However as the movie transitioned and slowed down I realized they were trying to fit in a movie and a half to make up for the half of a movie episode 8 was, and undo a lot of the damage done by it. I walked out of the theater rather impressed at how they were able to save beloved characters, add in cool force powers, and actually pulled off a decent ending.
It was a great end to the Star Wars saga
ok not great though better than last jedi but pails in comparison
much better than the last movie but lacked emotional connections.
I thought it was good, not great like several of the other Star Wars movies.

Best Star Wars movie of my lifetime, born in '85.
